{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"The conversation history passed to the LLM is trimmed to the most recent 10 messages when the full history exceeds the context window.","required_reality_check_level":"Integration","justification":"The risk is in module handoff (history manager/prompt builder -> LLM request payload), not just isolated trimming logic. No explicit real HTTP/subprocess/OS contract is required, and correctness does not depend on model output quality. Rejected System/Agentic because the behavior text is about payload construction before inference, not external contract validation or model judgment.","test_description":"Run the real request-construction path with a >10-message history and assert the actual outbound LLM payload contains exactly the most recent 10 messages in order.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.18,"Integration":0.72,"System":0.04,"Agentic":0.05,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"The generated response addresses the customer's question rather than producing a generic or off-topic reply.","required_reality_check_level":"Agentic","justification":"Correctness depends on real LLM output quality (relevance/on-topicness). A stubbed model would hide this failure class and can always be made to pass. Rejected Workflow because this behavior evaluates a single generation quality outcome, not a multi-agentic sequence requirement.","test_description":"Send representative customer questions to the real model path and evaluate whether responses are question-relevant (not generic/off-topic) using predefined quality criteria/human rubric.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.06,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.82,"Workflow":0.08}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"The tone re-check correctly identifies when a response is too formal for a casual-tier customer and triggers regeneration.","required_reality_check_level":"Workflow","justification":"This behavior spans multiple agentic steps in sequence: initial generation, tone judgment, then regeneration trigger. Failures can occur in model-driven handoff between stages; deterministic mocks can hide them. Rejected Agentic because one real model call is insufficient to validate the full chained decision/regen pipeline.","test_description":"Execute end-to-end on real model calls for casual-tier prompts likely to produce formal drafts, verify tone-check flags formality, and verify regeneration is actually invoked and completed in the same flow.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.0,"Integration":0.04,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.33,"Workflow":0.6}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"The full exchange (user message, generated response, any regenerations) is persisted to the database with correct timestamps.","required_reality_check_level":"Integration","justification":"This is cross-module persistence/state consistency (chat flow -> persistence layer -> DB readback). A local real DB integration check provides reality signal beyond unit tests. Rejected System because the behavior text does not require real external HTTP/subprocess contract checks; local DB round-trip is sufficient here.","test_description":"Run a chat interaction (including a forced regeneration case), then read persisted records from the test DB and assert all entries exist with correct ordering, linkage, and timestamps.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.05,"Integration":0.8,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"When the tone check triggers regeneration, the second response replaces the first — the customer never sees the rejected draft.","required_reality_check_level":"Workflow","justification":"This is a sequencing/handoff guarantee across agentic stages (draft generation -> tone decision -> regeneration -> final delivery). The correctness condition depends on multi-step orchestration with model-involved transitions; unit/integration fakes can miss leak-through timing/state bugs. Rejected System because no explicit requirement here to validate real external protocol/error contract; the core risk is multi-agentic pipeline behavior.","test_description":"Run the real multi-step chat pipeline in cases that trigger tone regeneration and assert the customer-facing output channel contains only the regenerated response while internal logs retain the rejected draft as non-delivered.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.0,"Integration":0.08,"System":0.07,"Agentic":0.2,"Workflow":0.65}}]}
